ZH: 1. 这个国家的蚕食行为正在侵蚀国家资源。
EN: The nation's act of encroachment is eroding its resources.
ZH: 2. 这家公司正在蚕食市场份额，吞并竞争对手。
EN: This company is nibbling away at market shares, swallowing its competitors.
ZH: 3. 这项政策的实施将蚕食我们的财政预算。
EN: The implementation of this policy will eat into our fiscal budget.
ZH: 4. 长期的优惠措施将蚕食公司的利润。
EN: Prolonged preferential measures will gnaw at the company's profits.
ZH: 5. 这项政策的影响逐渐蚕食了人们的信心。
EN: The impact of this policy has gradually eroded people's confidence.
ZH: 6. 近年来，环境的变化蚕食了该地区的生态系统。
EN: In recent years, the changes in the environment have nibbled away at the ecosystem of this region.
ZH: 7. 这种行为正在蚕食我们的文化遗产。
EN: This behavior is undermining our cultural heritage.
ZH: 8. 这个社会中的腐败正在蚕食人们的信任。
EN: The corruption in this society is eating away at people's trust.
ZH: 9. 他一点一点地蚕食了我的自尊心。
EN: He nibbled away at my self-esteem bit by bit.
ZH: 10. 不断涨价蚕食了我们每个人的购买力。
EN: The continuous price increases are eroding the purchasing power of each one of us.

ZH: 11. 这股洪流正在蚕食着这片土地的河岸。
EN: This torrent is eating into the riverbank of this land.
ZH: 12. 我们不能任由他蚕食我们的权益。
EN: We cannot allow him to nibble away at our rights.
ZH: 13. 蚕食的结果是逐渐削弱了我们的竞争力。
EN: The result of encroachment is gradually weakening our competitiveness.
ZH: 14. 没有采取措施，时间会慢慢蚕食我们的边境防线。
EN: Without taking measures, time will slowly erode our border defenses.
ZH: 15. 这种行为正在蚕食我们社区的社会纽带。
EN: This behavior is undermining the social cohesion of our community.
ZH: 16. 恶劣的天气正在蚕食农民的收成。
EN: The harsh weather is eating away at the farmers' harvest.
ZH: 17. 不断增长的成本正在蚕食电力公司的盈利。
EN: The continuously growing costs are eroding the profits of the power company.
ZH: 18. 长时间的工作压力会慢慢蚕食你的健康。
EN: Long hours of work pressure will slowly undermine your health.
ZH: 19. 密集的竞争正在蚕食着这个行业的利润率。
EN: Intense competition is nibbling away at the profit margins of this industry.
ZH: 20. 这种草木控制措施正在蚕食着该地区的生态平衡。
EN: This vegetation control measure is encroaching on the ecological balance of this region.
